{{Infobox writer | name = William Missouri Downs | birth_name = William Missouri Downs | birth_place = Bay City, Michigan | occupation = Dramatist, Screenwriter, Director | awards =Finalist at the Eugene O'Neill, Finalist – Reva Shiner Comedy Award, Larry Corse Prize For Playwriting, The Greenhouse Festival Of New Plays | notableworks = The Art of Theatre ([[Wadsworth Publishing|Wadsworth]]) Naked Playwriting (Silman/James) <!--into prose: | influences = [[Moss Hart]], [[Buster Keaton]], [[Anton Chekhov]], [[Voltaire]] & [[Schopenhauer]] --> }} '''William Missouri Downs''' is an American playwright, screenwriter, director, author and university professor.
==Education== He holds an M.F.A. in acting from the University of Illinois and an M.F.A. in screenwriting from U.C.L.A. He was trained in playwriting by Pulitzer Prize-winning playwright Lanford Wilson (5 July, Talley's Folly), in screenwriting by Oscar-winning screenwriter Stirling Silliphant (In the Heat of the Night, The Poseidon Adventure) and in directing by Oscar-nominated director Jerzy Antczak (Nights and Days). Bill also spent several years studying playwriting with Milan Stitt (Yale School of Drama) at The Circle Rep Theatre in New York City. ==Career== ===Playwriting=== His plays have been produced by the Orlando Shakespeare Theatre,<ref>http://www.orlandoshakes.org/plays-events/the-exit-interview.html</ref> the Wisdom Bridge Theatre in Chicago, the New York City Fringe Festival, [[InterAct Theatre Company|The InterAct Theatre]] in Philadelphia,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://interacttheatre.org/|title=Home|website=InterAct Theatre Company|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref> [[San Diego Repertory Theatre|The San Diego Rep]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sdrep.org/|title=San Diego Repertory Theatre - Stage Plays, Theater Events, Musicals, Concerts, Casting Auditions, Jobs|website=www.sdrep.org|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref> the Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts (as part of the AT&T Performing Arts Festival), The Berkeley Repertory Theatre, the Salt Lake City Acting Company, the Actors Theatre of Charlotte, the International Theatre Festival in Israel, the Stadt Theater Walfischgasse in Austria, the Detroit Rep, the Durban Performing Arts Center in South Africa, and over 150 other theatres worldwide. ===Screen=== In Hollywood, Bill started as a script secretary on NBC's ''Moonlighting'' (Bruce Willis and Cybill Shepherd), and his acceptance into the prestigious Warner Brothers Sitcom Writing Workshop paved his way as a staff writer on NBC's ''[[My Two Dads]]'' (Paul Reiser). He also wrote episodes for the NBC shows ''Amen'' (Sherman Hemsley) and ''[[Fresh Prince Of Bel Air]]'' (Will Smith). In addition he sold a movie to Ron Howard's [[Imagine Entertainment|Imagine Films]] and optioned another to [[Filmways]]. While a student at UCLA film school, Bill won numerous screenwriting awards, including the Jack Nicholson prize.
==Awards== Downs<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.williammissouridowns.com|title=William Missouri Downs|website=William Missouri Downs|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref> has won two rolling premieres from the National New Play Network [[National New Play Network]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nnpn.org/about/people/playwrights|title=About - National New Play Network|website=www.nnpn.org|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref> and twice been a finalist at the Eugene O'Neill.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sites.google.com/a/theoneill.org/npc-2013-finalists/mad-gravity-by-william-missouri-downs|title=Mad Gravity by William Missouri Downs - 2013 National Playwrights Conference Finalists|website=sites.google.com|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nnpn.org/affiliated-artists/playwrights|title=Playwrights - National New Play Network|website=nnpn.org|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref> He also won the Beverly Hills Theatre Guild Julie Harris Award <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://beverlyhillstheatreguild.com/present_winners.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2017-03-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170326051649/http://www.beverlyhillstheatreguild.com/present_winners.html |archive-date=2017-03-26 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
